owl:Ontology.dc:title: Ontology Describing terminological and ontological Knowledge resources
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: This is a new version of our Ontology, we have changed the way of representing resources, we are focusing on the fact that a resource may have different models of representations and then we have added a new class called TOK_Model that plays the role of classifying the resources, so we consider everything as a resource and the way to classify them is when thay use a certain model to be represented. We have then amodels representing ontological resources, others representing terminological resources, etc. Somehow we are just applying the main idea about our approach to ensure the openness of our ontology or global model to all kinds of resources.
Updated on October 1st 2014 by Nizar Ghoula

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: this relation is an abstraction of the treatment of TOK resources using different TOK tools in many fields in order to perform a task using TOK resources on other resources like ontology driven annotation, or using TOK resources on TOK resources like resoning and chek consistency.
this property describes the relation between a TOK resource and the task or the usage it may be pertinent for.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: this class is an abstraction of the alignment that may exist between two TOK resources.
a type of topic which models the concept represented by a collection of synonymous terms in a thesaurus.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Corpus
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: this class is a description of the concept corpus which is a terminological resource
this is an abstraction of different tools that may be applied on TOK resources. The usage of tools may be various relatively to the nature of the task to perform and the nature of the resource.
This class is an abstraction of a Terminological and Ontological resource that is used for knowledge management and engineering.
This class describes the register of language covered by the corpus in use, the type of its value is a domain restriction or a specific type of tasks that describes a field of a domain.
Language class is an abstraction of the language covered by a terminological resource it has a value in a list of languages.
this class represents an abstraction of the formalism of representation used to describe knowledge.

Task or Usage, this class describes the tasks performed on/by a terminological resource, we can make a discrimination between both tasks but in our case of use these actions or tasks may be performed using TOK resources on TOK resources. Each task is iplemented by an operator.
a type of topic which models a single term in a resource. in a thesaurus a term is a single word or a phrase.

This class describes the period or the intervall of time in which the language used in the corpus evoluates. this classi is important becaus it gives precision about the vitality of a language and is an important caracteristic of a corpus.
